text: Johann Georg, Prince von Hohenzollern (Johann Georg Carl Leopold Eitel- Friedrich Meinrad Maria Hubertus Michael; 31 July 1932 – 2 March 2016) was a German prince. Through his marriage to Princess Birgitta of Sweden, he was brother-in-law of King Carl XVI Gustaf of Sweden. Prince Johann Georg was the sixth child of Frederick, Prince of Hohenzollern (30 August 1891 – 6 February 1965) and his wife Princess Margarete Karola of Saxony (24 January 1900 – 16 October 1962). Goerg died on 2 March 2016 in Munich.
